! ============================================================================
! X11 KEY REMAPPING CONFIGURATION
! ============================================================================
! Purpose:
!   Remap the Print Screen key to act as an additional Super (Windows) key
!   This gives you a Super key on the right side of the keyboard
!
! How it works:
!   1. Clears the Print function from keycode 107 (PrtSc key)
!   2. Assigns Super_L to keycode 107
!   3. Adds keycode 107 to the mod4 (Super) modifier group
!
! Usage:
!   This file is loaded automatically by bspwmrc on startup
!   Manual reload: xmodmap ~/.Xmodmap
!
! Verification:
!   After loading, PrtSc will work with all Super+ keybindings in SXHKD
!   Test with: Super+Enter (should open terminal with PrtSc+Enter)
!
! Related Files:
!   - ~/.config/bspwm/bspwmrc (loads this file on startup)
!   - ~/.config/sxhkd/sxhkdrc (defines Super+ keybindings)
! ============================================================================

! Remove Print from keycode 107 (Print Screen key)
keycode 107 = NoSymbol NoSymbol NoSymbol NoSymbol

! Map keycode 107 to Super_L
keycode 107 = Super_L

! Ensure keycode 107 is in the Super modifier group (mod4)
! First clear the modifier to avoid conflicts
clear mod4
! Add all Super keys to mod4 (including our remapped PrtSc)
add mod4 = Super_L Super_R Hyper_L